Greetings Self Development Academy Families,

We hope you and your family are well. The 2019-2020 school year is rapidly coming to a close. At this time, we want to remind you that if your student checked out any library books and/or textbooks to please return them to the school's Front Office by Friday, June 5.

Also, we are making arrangements for your child's classroom belongings to be returned to you. More details to follow.

If you have any questions, please contact the Front Office at (480) 641-2640.

Thank you,

Self Development Academy - Mesa

ï¿¼MINI CHALLENGE - WRITE YOUR PASSION. 24hrs.

Recently, Fordham Professor of English and Creative Writing Caroline Hagood asked her students what would move them so much as to write on the nearest thing possible, as MLK had done writing his famous â€œLetters from Birmingham Jailâ€ on top of old newspaper.

What would move you and your children so much to write on the nearest thing possible? Prove it in this mini challenge. Write a short simple statement about some belief, value, or idea that would inspire you to write vigorously on anything nearby. Eg the above MLK example, paper napkins and musical riffs for musicians, back of hand and poets. Make it brief but write with passion. Points for writing it with creative materials and/or on creative (but adult approved) surfaces.

#poetry #beauty #injustice #humanity #hope #community #whateversinyourheart
